File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function kurtosis_f m n,  Next: Function kurtosis_gamma a b,  Prev: Function kurtosis_exp m,  Up: distrib

 -- Function: kurtosis_f (M, N)
     Returns the kurtosis coefficient of a F random variable F(m,n),
     with m>0, n>8.  To make use of this function, write first
     ‘load("distrib")’.

     The kurtosis coefficient is

     KU[X] = 12{m(n+m-2)(5n-22) + (n-4)(n-2)^2 \over m(n-8)(n-6)(n+m-2)}

