 -- Function: kurtosis_weibull (A, B)
     Returns the kurtosis coefficient of a {\it Weibull}(a,b) random
     variable, with a,b>0.  To make use of this function, write first
     ‘load("distrib")’.

     The kurtosis coefficient is

     KU[X] = { \Gamma_4 - 4\Gamma_1 \Gamma_3 + 6\Gamma_1^2 \Gamma_2 - 3
     \Gamma_1^4 \over \left[\Gamma_2 - \Gamma_1^2\right]^2 } - 3

     KU[X] = { \Gamma_4 - 4\Gamma_1 \Gamma_3 + 6\Gamma_1^2 \Gamma_2 - 3
     \Gamma_1^4 \over \left[\Gamma_2 - \Gamma_1^2\right]^2 } - 3

     where \Gamma_k = \Gamma\left(1+k/a\right).


