 -- Function: quantile_beta (Q, A, B)
     Returns the _q_-quantile of a {\it Beta}(a,b) random variable, with
     a,b>0; in other words, this is the inverse of ‘cdf_beta’.  Argument
     _q_ must be an element of [0,1].  To make use of this function,
     write first ‘load("distrib")’.


