 -- Function: quantile_poisson (Q, M)
     Returns the _q_-quantile of a {\it Poisson}(m) random variable,
     with m>0; in other words, this is the inverse of ‘cdf_poisson’.
     Argument _q_ must be an element of [0,1].  To make use of this
