     The \chi^2(n) random variable is equivalent to the
     \Gamma\left(n/2,2\right) .

     The skewness coefficient is

     SK[X] = \sqrt{8\over n}

     SK[X] = \sqrt{8\over n}

     (%i1) load ("distrib")$
     
     (%i2) skewness_chi2(n);
