 -- Function: skewness_gumbel (A, B)
     Returns the skewness coefficient of a {\it Gumbel}(a,b) random
     variable, with b>0.

     The skewness coefficient is

     SK[X] = {12\sqrt{6}\over \pi^3} \zeta(3)

     SK[X] = {12\sqrt{6}\over \pi^3} \zeta(3)

     (%i1) load ("distrib")$
     
