     The {\it Rayleigh}(b) random variable is equivalent to the {\it
     Weibull}(2,1/b) .

     The skewness coefficient is

     SK[X] = {2\sqrt{\pi}(\pi - 3)\over (4-\pi)^{3/2}}

     SK[X] = {2\sqrt{\pi}(\pi - 3)\over (4-\pi)^{3/2}}

