File: maxima-core-docs.info,  Node: Function skewness_weibull a b,  Next: Function std_bernoulli p,  Prev: Function skewness_student_t n,  Up: distrib

 -- Function: skewness_weibull (A, B)
     Returns the skewness coefficient of a {\it Weibull}(a,b) random
     variable, with a,b>0.  To make use of this function, write first
     ‘load("distrib")’.

     The skewness coefficient is

     SK[X] = {\displaystyle\Gamma\left(1+{3\over a}\right)
     -3\Gamma\left(1+{1\over a}\right)\Gamma\left(1+{2\over
     a}\right)+2\Gamma\left(1+{1\over a}\right)^3 \over
     \displaystyle\left[\Gamma\left(1+{2\over
     a}\right)-\Gamma\left(1+{1\over a}\right)^2\right]^{3/2} }

     SK[X] = {\displaystyle\Gamma\left(1+{3\over a}\right)
     -3\Gamma\left(1+{1\over a}\right)\Gamma\left(1+{2\over
     a}\right)+2\Gamma\left(1+{1\over a}\right)^3 \over
     \displaystyle\left[\Gamma\left(1+{2\over
     a}\right)-\Gamma\left(1+{1\over a}\right)^2\right]^{3/2} }


